{"type":"answer","id":228550,"parentType":"question","parentId":22379,"uid":26159,"contents":"原因很简单，人口结构不同。城市地区<b>大多</b>是民主党的票仓，农村地区<b>大多</b>是共和党的票仓。我之前所在的州，在地图上就是遍地红中几点蓝，只有都市和几个大学城是蓝的。<br>\n<br>\n而我们知道，城市地区高人口密度必然更容易发生传染病。<br>\n<br>\n如果你看小选区会更明显：<br>\n<a href=\"https://i.imgur.com/FavJmoN.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/FavJmoN.jpg\" alt=\"https://i.imgur.com/FavJmoN.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></a><br>\n<a href=\"https://i.imgur.com/pcc0uUP.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pcc0uUP.png\" alt=\"https://i.imgur.com/pcc0uUP.png\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></a><br>\n<br>\n高人口密度和蓝色有相当的重叠。<br>\n<br>\n所以疫情和选票方向之间有什么关系？<b>大概是全球变暖和海盗减少之间的那种关系</b>。<br>\n<a href=\"https://i.imgur.com/UHIMF6O.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/UHIMF6O.jpg\" alt=\"https://i.imgur.com/UHIMF6O.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></a>","date":"2020-04-04","agreeCount":21,"discussionCount":1}